{"questionId":"17366","questionHtml":"<p>Find the equation of the horizontal asymptote of the graph.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p \\to \\infty&nbsp; \\Rightarrow {\\text{cos}}\\,\\theta&nbsp; \\to \\frac{1}{2}\"> <mi>p</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>θ</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence the asymptote has equation <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\theta&nbsp; = \\frac{\\pi }{3}\"> <mi>θ</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mi>π</mi> <mn>3</mn> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17366","referenceCode":"19N.1.AHL.TZ0.H_11c.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the equation of the horizontal asymptote of the graph.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}